Online-softmax fusion for attention decode kernel

## Status
Proposed

## Goal
Fuse score computation + weighted sum in rocm_attn_decode_heads_kernel into a single KV cache read using online safe-softmax, eliminating the second KV read that currently doubles bandwidth.

## Context
File: ds4_rocm.c:5305, `rocm_attn_decode_heads_kernel`

Current kernel reads KV cache twice per decode step per head:
- Step 1 (L5332-5345): dot product q-kv for each KV slot -> scores
- Step 5 (L5383-5393): weighted sum re-reads all KV slots x head_dim

For ~8K+ KV slots x 128 head_dim this doubles ~all attention bandwidth.

Online safe-softmax algorithm sketch:
- Single pass over KV: compute score, track running max + exp-difference-weighted sum
- Store partial accumulators per dimension in registers
- Finalize after the loop

Hardware: gfx1151, 40 CUs, wave32, LDS <=16 KiB, head_dim=128, n_head=32

## Affected functions
- rocm_attn_decode_heads_kernel (kernel)
- ds4_metal_attention_decode_heads_tensor (wrapper, L5396)
- Possibly the batch variants at L5971, L6000, L6036

## Validation
1. DS4_ROCM=1 make ds4 ds4_rocm_kernel_test
2. ./ds4_rocm_kernel_test - must end with OK
3. End-to-end decode: time ./ds4 --backend rocm -p "..." -n 200 --temp 0 --seed 42
4. Compare token throughput before/after with DS4_ROCM_TIME=1
5. Numerics must match: raw score diff < 1e-5 fudge from safe-softmax reordering

## Next steps
1. Prototype fused kernel variant alongside existing one
2. Gate behind env var (DS4_ROCM_ATTN_FUSED=1)
3. Benchmark: same q/kv, compare output diffs and throughput
4. If quality passes, replace old kernel